Interface VFunctionsAndVUnboundMethods.VFunction<A,R>

  • Type Parameters:
    A - the generic type of the argument, with VoidA as a possibility
    R - the generic type of the return value, with VoidR as a possibility
    All Superinterfaces:
    Function<A,R>
    Enclosing interface:
    VFunctionsAndVUnboundMethods
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public static interface VFunctionsAndVUnboundMethods.VFunction<A,R>
extends Function<A,R>
    A "voidable" functional interface which takes no arg or a single arg which may be of any generic type <A> including VoidA and returns a value of any generic type <R> including VoidR.

    Function objects of the following types may be converted to this type:

    1. Runnable -> VFunction<VoidA,VoidR>
    2. Callable<R> -> VFunction<VoidA,R>
    3. Supplier<R> -> VFunction<VoidA,R>
    4. Consumer<A> -> VFunction<A,VoidR>
    5. Function<A,R> -> VFunction<A,R>
    VFunctions made from Runnable, Callable<R> and Supplier<R> may be called either with no arg or with single arg voidA; VFunctions made from Consumer<A> and Function<A,R> are called with one arg of generic type <A>.

    VFunctions made from Runnable and Consumer<A> return voidR; VFunctions made from Callable<R>, Supplier<R> and Function<A,R> return objects of generic type <R>.
